quran[61]{c,v,t}:
  37,22,"“Bring up,” it will be said, “The wrongdoers and their partners, and the things they worshipped"
  37,23,"“Besides God, and lead them to the way of the fire"
  37,24,"“But stop them, for they must be asked"
  37,25,“What is the matter with you that you did not help each other?”
  37,26,"No, but that day they will submit"
  37,27,"And they will turn to one another, and question each other"
  37,28,"They will say, “It was you who used to come to us from the right.”"
  37,29,"They will reply, “No, you yourselves had no faith"
  37,30,"“Nor had we any authority over you. No, it was you who were a people in obstinate rebellion"
  37,31,"“So now has been proved true against us, the word of our Lord, so we will indeed taste it"
  37,32,"“We led you astray, for indeed we were ourselves astray.”"
  37,33,"Indeed that day, they will all share in the penalty"
  37,34,Indeed that is how We will deal with the wrong-doers
  37,35,"For they, when they were told that there is no god except God, would puff themselves up with pride–"
  37,36,"And say, “What, will we give up our gods for the sake of a poet possessed?”"
  37,37,"No, he has come with the truth, and he confirms the messengers"
  37,38,You will indeed taste the terrible penalty
  37,39,But it will be no more than retribution for what you did
  37,40,But the sincere servants of God
  37,41,For them is sustenance determined
  37,42,"They will enjoy fruits, and honor and dignity"
  37,43,In gardens of felicity
  37,44,Facing each other on thrones
  37,45,Round will be passed to them a cup from a clear-flowing fountain
  37,46,"White, of a taste delicious to those who drink of it"
  37,47,"Free from harm, nor will they suffer intoxication from it"
  37,48,And with them will be companions of modest gaze and beautiful eyes
  37,49,Like delicate eggs closely guarded
  37,50,Then they will turn to one another and question each other
  37,51,"One of them will start the conversation by saying, “I had a friend"
  37,52,"“Who used to say, ‘What, are you among those who bear witness to the truth"
  37,53,"“When we die and become dust and bones, will we indeed receive rewards and punishments?”"
  37,54,"A voice said, “Would you like to look down?”"
  37,55,He looked down and saw him in the middle of the fire
  37,56,"He said, “By God, you were just short of bringing me to perdition"
  37,57,"“Had it not been for the grace of my Lord, I would certainly have been among those sent there"
  37,58,“Is it the case that we will not die
  37,59,"“Except our first death, and that we will not be punished?”"
  37,60,Indeed this is the greatest achievement
  37,61,For the like of this let all strive who wish to strive
  37,62,Is that the better entertainment or the Tree of Zaqqum
  37,63,For We have truly made it a trial for the wrongdoers
  37,64,For it is a tree that springs out of the bottom of hellfire
  37,65,The shoots of its fruit-stalks are like the heads of devils
  37,66,Truly they will eat of it and fill their stomachs
  37,67,Then indeed on top of that they will be given a mixture made of boiling water
  37,68,Then their return will be to the fire
  37,69,Truly they found their parents on the wrong path
  37,70,So they were rushed down on their footsteps
  37,71,"And truly before them, many of the ancients went astray"
  37,72,"But We sent among them, people to advise them"
  37,73,Then see what was the end of those who were advised
  37,74,Except the sincere servants of God
  37,75,"Noah called to Us, and We are the best to hear prayers"
  37,76,And We delivered him and his people from the Great Calamity
  37,77,And made his progeny to endure
  37,78,And We left for him generations to come in later times
  37,79,Peace and salutation to Noah among the nations
  37,80,Indeed we reward those who do right
  37,81,For he was one of our believing servants
  37,82,Then the rest we overwhelmed in the flood